“This has nothing to do with Covid-19 — just with cleanliness in the house,” he said.
The same reasoning applies to changing out of clothing you’ve worn outside once you’re indoors, he said.
If possible, try to plan for two weeks worth of meals and any other essentials to limit the number of trips needed for more supplies.
If you’re able to, stock up on at least a 30-day supply of any necessary prescriptions as well.
Even if you appear healthy, assume you’ve come into contact with the virus and wash your hands before interacting with them.